# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code uses a common JavaScript obfuscation pattern with:
1. A string array (`a0_0x24ea`) containing base64-encoded strings
2. A decoder function (`a0_0x2439`) that decodes and caches strings
3. A self-executing shuffler that rearranges the string array until a checksum matches
4. Obfuscated property names and control flow (switch-case with string-split patterns)

## Deobfuscated Code

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // ~2π
const PHI = 1.618;          // Golden ratio
const SQRT1_2 = 0.707;      // ~√(1/2)

// Simulation configuration
const config = {
    gravity: 4000,           // Repulsion strength between nodes
    stiffness: 0.004,        // Spring stiffness (default)
    dampingFriction: 0.92,   // Velocity damping per frame
    centering: 0.0003,       // Force pulling nodes toward center
    particleRate: 40,        // Max number of particles
    particleSpeed: 0.04,     // Particle speed decay factor
    deltaTime: 0.06          // Time step
};

// ============ NODES ============
const nodes = [
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "zeta",    label: "Zeta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ============ EDGES (Springs) ============
const edges = [
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "zeta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "beta",  b: "zeta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "beta",  b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// ============ CAMERA ============
let camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// ============ PARTICLES ============
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// ============ PHYSICS SIMULATION ============
function simulate() {
    // 1) Node-node repulsion (Coulomb-like force)
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            let force = config.gravity / (dist * dist);
            let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            let fy = (dy / dist) * force;

            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Spring forces along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        let nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        let nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        let dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        let dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        let displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        let force = (edges[i].k || config.stiffness) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) Apply damping, centering force, and integrate positions
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        // Damping (friction)
        nodes[i].vx *= config.dampingFriction;
        nodes[i].vy *= config.dampingFriction;

        // Centering force (pulls toward 400, 300)
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centering;
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centering;

        // Integrate position
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// ============ SPAWN PARTICLES ============
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.particleRate) return;

    let sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    let angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2
    });
}

// ============ UPDATE PARTICLES ============
function updateParticles() {
    for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        let p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.particleSpeed * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.particleSpeed * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// ============ SMOOTH CAMERA ============
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.deltaTime;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.deltaTime;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.deltaTime;
}

// ============ MAIN LOOP ============
function tick() {
    simulate();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout simulation** — the kind used to visualize network/graph data. Here's the summary:

### Core Mechanics
| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **6 Nodes** | Named Alpha, Beta, Zeta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon — each with position, velocity, and radius |
| **8 Edges** | Springs connecting node pairs with rest lengths and stiffness constants |
| **Repulsion** | Every pair of nodes repels each other (inverse-square law, like electrical charges) |
| **Springs** | Connected nodes are pulled together/pushed apart via Hooke's law toward a rest length |
| **Centering** | A gentle force pulls all nodes toward the center point (400, 300) |
| **Damping** | Velocity is multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent oscillation |
| **Particles** | Decorative particles spawn from random nodes, drift outward, and fade/die over time |
| **Camera** | Smoothly interpolates toward a target position/zoom (easing) |

### In short:
> **It's a physics-based animated node graph** that arranges itself organically through repulsion + spring forces, with ambient floating particles for visual flair. It runs at ~60 FPS with no rendering code included — this is purely the **simulation/logic layer** (rendering to a canvas would be handled elsewhere).
